treeview

Interface ITreeNode<TREETYPE>

  • Type Parameters:
    TREETYPE - The type of the underlying element (data of the node). This type is replaced with the specific type during instantiation.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GenericTreeNode, GroupTreeNode, ItemTreeNode

    public interface ITreeNode<TREETYPE>
    Specifies the behavior of a node in the GenericTreeView. It provides methods to set the underlying value of the node (the data), as well as methods to retrieve its child-nodes. Furthermore it specifies a method to find items (nodes) in the tree and generate a meaningful output for a console application
    Author:
    OOP

      • findItem

        <T> ITreeNode<TREETYPE> findItem(T item)
        This method traverses the tree and searches for the passed item passed. The passed argument identifies the item that should be found. If a node is found, the return value is the treenode, otherwise it is null. The comparison between the passed item and the current node is based on the method checkItem(T). The method itself contains a typeparameter T which makes the passed argument generic. This typeparameter is replaced with the specific type during method call.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the passed item
        Parameters:
        item - The specific item that we try to find
        Returns:
        the treenode if found, or null if it can't be found

      • checkItem

        <T> boolean checkItem(T item)
        This method checks the current node against a passed item. If the passed item matches the current node (e.g. the node is the same as the item or the underlying property of the node is equal to the passed item) then true is returned. Otherwise false is returned. The type of the item is determined during the method call and thus a typeparameter is used.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the passed item
        Parameters:
        item - The specific item that is checked
        Returns:
        true if the passed item is matching the current node, false otherwise

      • generateConsoleView

        String generateConsoleView(String spacer,
                           String preamble)
        Generates a string containing all the entries in the tree. It allows to pass a spacer argument which is used to separate the entries in the tree and a preamble which specifies the leading characters of the current entry.
        Parameters:
        spacer - The string that should be used to separate entries in the tree
        preamble - specifies the leading characters of the current entry
        Returns:
        the string output of the tree
